Xinhua Review: Turning Outstanding Returning Migrant Workers into a New Force for Rural Revitalization-Xinhuanet
Talents are the key to rural revitalization.
Where to find talents?
Outstanding returning migrant workers are an indispensable new force.
Xinhua News Agency issued Hai Chunzuo
Xinhua News Agency, Chengdu, July 26 (Xinhua) Title: Turning outstanding returning migrant workers into a new force for rural revitalization
Zhang Xiong, 34, lives in Orchard Village, Meishan City, Sichuan Province. In 2010, he quit his job in Beijing with a monthly salary of tens of thousands and returned home to start a business.
After several years of hard work, the annual income of the grape-growing family farm he runs now exceeds one million yuan, and he has become a well-known leader in getting rich. He has also been selected into the "two committees" of the village.
In recent years, inspired by a series of policies to support agriculture and benefit agriculture, such as national poverty alleviation and rural revitalization, more and more outstanding migrant workers like Zhang Xiong have chosen to return home to start their own businesses, activating a pool of spring water in the countryside.
Sichuan, a province with a large population and a large labor export in western China, has implemented the "Outstanding Migrant Workers Return Training Project" according to the situation. In 2019 alone, more than 8,000 village party branch secretaries, 61,000 village reserve forces and more than 20,000 party members have been generated from the outstanding migrant workers, providing a strong guarantee for winning the battle against poverty and implementing the rural revitalization strategy.
Well-off is not well-off, the key depends on the villagers.
Since the reform and opening up, a large number of young and middle-aged laborers in rural China have gone out to work to increase their income, and some have set up their own enterprises through hard work.
However, objectively, it also leads to the "hollowing out" of rural areas to varying degrees, especially the weakening of rural grass-roots organizations. The village party branch secretaries and party members all show the characteristics of "one old and one low," that is, aging, low academic qualifications, weak village party organization leaders, and outstanding problems.
If rural talents and other factors have been flowing to the city in one direction, and the countryside has been in a state of "blood loss" and "anemia" for a long time, revitalization is empty talk.
Attract those migrant workers who are capable, conscious and interested in serving their hometown, guide them to return home to start businesses and become rich leaders, train them to become party members and rural cadres on the basis of merit, and enrich the ranks of grass-roots cadres. This is the fundamental solution to the problem that the ranks of rural party members and grass-roots party organizations are not connected with each other.
Excellent migrant workers should be brought back, and they should be kept and done well.
In recent years, Sichuan has started with paying close attention to the party building of migrant workers. On the basis of strict selection criteria, it has established institutional mechanisms such as directional introduction, service guarantee, training, selection and use of outstanding migrant workers, so that they can improve their abilities, have security in their work, have hope in their lives, really take root in the countryside, and have a sense of accomplishment in starting a business.
This year is the end of the decisive battle against poverty. Talents are the key factor in the connection between poverty alleviation and rural revitalization.
Party committees and governments at all levels should attach great importance to the group of outstanding returning migrant workers, and through comprehensive measures, turn them into a task force and a new force that can stay, fight and cannot be taken away, so as to provide strong organizational guarantee and talent support for rural poverty alleviation, well-off development and revitalization.
