Pursuing the Poetic "Yellow River Dream" -Zhongxin.com
(China's Poverty Reduction Story) Pursuing the Poetic "Yellow River Dream"
China News Service, Yinchuan, July 26 (Yang Di) "Jiuqu Yellow River thousands of miles of sand, waves and winds from the end of the world."
The Yellow River, which aroused the pride of countless literati, gave birth to the beautiful and rich Ningxia Plain. Nowadays, Ningxia, which has the reputation of "blocking the south of the Yangtze River," is adhering to the concept of "ecological priority and green development" and pursuing the poetic "Yellow River Dream."
River clear water beautiful "blue wave dream"
"The Yellow River in the world is rich in Ningxia," and the Yellow River flows 397 kilometers through Ningxia, which is the "mother river" that nurtures one side.
However, with the rapid advancement of industrialization and urbanization, the development, utilization, management and protection of rivers and lakes are out of balance, and chaos such as excessive sewage discharge, reclamation of lakes and encroachment on water areas are highlighted, resulting in black and smelly water bodies, excessive water quality, dirty environment and ecological degradation.
Now, Ningxia is promoting the diverse restoration of water ecology and striving to return the Yellow River to its beautiful and clear waters.
Water control should start from the source.
In Yinchuan, Ningxia, the local government adopted the method of "standard raising + pollution control + strict management." All sewage in the industrial park was treated centrally, all urban sewage treatment plants were discharged according to Class A standard, and the black and smelly water bodies in the urban built-up areas were basically eliminated. The third batch of China's black and smelly water demonstration cities were successfully declared.
In addition, Ningxia fully implemented the river and lake chief system in 2017, and now it has achieved full coverage of the five-level river and lake chief responsibility system in districts, cities, counties and villages, and long river patrols have become the norm.
Gu Jincheng, 64, lives in a village by the Yellow River. He witnessed the changes of the Yellow River: "The water used to smell bad, but the smell disappeared after remediation."
Gu Jincheng said that the ecological environment is better and his life is more comfortable. Now he often goes for a walk along the Yellow River with his family to feel the clear water and blue sky.
Sha Luoxiangji's "Wetland Dream"
Birds, green trees, plank roads, clear water... The beautiful scenery of Fan Zhongyan's "Sha Luoxiangji" has become a reality in the Yellow River Wetland Park in Yinchuan, Ningxia.
The Yellow River flows through Ningxia, forming river wetlands, lake wetlands, marsh wetlands and other wetlands along the way, which plays an important role in promoting the rational utilization of water resources and water ecological balance, and has also become an important international bird migration channel.
Since 2009, relevant departments in Ningxia have invested about 3.45 billion yuan in wetland protection projects. At present, Yinchuan wetland covers an area of 19,200 hectares, with a wetland protection rate of 78.5%. There are nearly 200 natural lakes and marshes, with 5 national wetland parks, 1 national urban wetland park, 6 autonomous region-level wetland parks and 8 municipal parks.
Lu Jinhu, deputy director of Yinchuan Wetland Protection Center, told reporters that wetland protection has increased biodiversity, especially in birds. "The gull is an endangered bird, with only more than 20,000 in the world, of which more than 2,000 live in Yinchuan Wetland."
At the same time, Ningxia has demarcated a 500-meter red line for the wetland protection area on both sides of the Yinchuan section of the Yellow River according to law, stipulating that no unit or individual may carry out development, construction and business activities within the scope of protection except for public welfare projects.
Zhao Shaoyong, deputy director of Yinchuan Water Conservancy Service Center, said that through pollution source control, comprehensive improvement of river and lake ecology and terminal wetland construction, the water quality of nine main drainage ditches in Ningxia has reached Class A standard by 100%. "Now the water is clear, the fish are swimming, and the flowers are blooming."
The "Drinking Water Dream" of Benefit People's Livelihood
Yinchuan City in Ningxia once had an "embarrassing" title: the only city along the Yellow River that "guarded the Yellow River and lacked water to drink."
Since 2010, Yinchuan City has been facing the problem of persistent water shortage in the summer peak. The "pain of water shortage" in the past ten years has become a painful experience for many high-rise residents in summer. However, under the current situation that the major water sources are at the limit of over-exploitation and the urban underground has formed a large area of groundwater over-exploitation funnel area, water shortage has become a difficult problem perplexing Yinchuan City.
Thanks to the improvement of the water quality of the Yellow River, drinking purified Yellow River water has become a good way to solve the drinking water problem of local residents.
Ding Ming, deputy director of Yinchuan Water Affairs Bureau, said that in order to improve the living and production water demand of urban and rural residents in Yinchuan, Ningxia launched the water supply project on the western line of urban and rural areas in Yinchuan metropolitan area in due course, replacing the original underground water source with high-quality Yellow River water.
"On December 29, 2019, the water supply project officially provided water to the three districts of Yinchuan City. In 2020, residents of Minning Town and Helan County also drank the Yellow River."
Ding Ming said that the Yinchuan water conservancy department will consider the transformation of the integration of regional rural drinking water and urban water supply. "In the next step, we will integrate all the scattered water supply points in rural areas into the western water supply project. It is expected that the integrated urban and rural water supply in Yinchuan region will be basically realized by the end of this year."
