In order to encourage residents to do physical examinations frequently and find problems as early as possible, the above-mentioned draft for comments proposes that the health department should formulate a basic catalogue of health examination items according to different ages, occupations and other factors.
The health examination expenses within the scope of the basic catalogue of health examination items shall be paid by the social medical insurance fund according to the standard of once a year per person.
