In addition, the employer should be equipped with full-time and part-time health management personnel, and regularly organize and carry out employee health check-ups.
With regard to the physical and mental health of minors, the draft for comments proposes that the sale of alcoholic beverages to minors is prohibited, and the sales location of alcoholic beverages is restricted. For those who violate the regulations, the market supervision and administration department will order them to make corrections and impose a fine of 30,000 yuan.
In addition to "prohibition of alcohol," minors should also "exercise more."
According to the requirements of the draft, schools should arrange students' sports activities for more than one hour every day.
For online games, public security, culture, radio, television, tourism, sports, network supervision, health and other departments should improve the health supervision system of Internet service business premises, establish a health review system for online games, and create a good communication space and culture for promoting the healthy growth of teenagers.
In addition, the draft also proposes that influenza patients must wear masks when entering and leaving public places, and medical and health institutions will be fined 20,000 yuan for disclosing patients' privacy without consent.
It is worth noting that in addition to the physical and mental health of residents, the draft also requires that Shenzhen departments should assess the impact of public policy implementation on the health of the population before formulating plans and normative documents involving urban spatial planning and construction, industrial park planning and construction, resource development and utilization and ecological environmental protection, and biomedical industry development, as well as approving major construction projects and implementing major public service projects.
If it has not been assessed or will have a serious adverse impact on urban public health or residents' health, it shall not be formulated, promulgated or approved for implementation.
