With the decline of Yu'e Bao's income, the "post-90s" not only did not escape Yu'e Bao, but began to "retaliate" to save money?
The "Yu'ebao Post-90s Savings Report" (2020 Edition) recently released by the China New Economic Research Institute and Alipay shows that in the first half of the year, the "post-90s" prefer to save money: the amount of money saved per capita increased by nearly 40% compared with 2019.
Interestingly, the "post-90s" are more likely to save from a small sum of money, with 60% of the average amount of money saved below 20 yuan...
Saving money with Yu'e Bao has also become the saving habit of the "post-90s."
Data show that of the 700 million Yu'e Bao users, 134 million are "post-90s."
There are 174 million "post-90s" in China, that is to say, about 3 out of every 4 "post-90s" in the country are saving money with Yu'e Bao.
At present, the 7-day annualized rate of return of money funds such as Yu'e Bao has fallen to about 1.5% from a level higher than 2% at the beginning of the year.
Even so, it did not affect the pace of saving money for the "post-90s."
Under the background of the promotion of Yu'e Bao's "saving effect," many young people who are used to using Yu'e Bao have also been directly transformed into "basic people."
According to Alipay data, as of July 13, the number of new "basic people" on Alipay has more than doubled year-on-year in the past month, and more and more young people have realized "advanced" financial management on Alipay.
Some analysts believe that the inflow of funds from Yu'e Bao into the stock market is also an important reason for the clear decline in the share of monetary funds in June.
The report also shows that "post-90s" girls are more likely to save more money, with an average of 20% higher than that of boys. Among the users who hold funds on Alipay platform, 60% are men, and women tend to choose more robust financial management methods than men.
After saving money, what are the plans of the post-90s generation?
Alipay data shows that the "post-90s" have the habit of saving money for their goals, with the largest number of users taking travel as their goal of saving money.
Affected by the epidemic, many "post-90s" save money to prepare for travel after the epidemic; the reopening of cinemas also provides a new way to switch from saving money to consumption.
