The overall stability of employment and prices shows that the economy has "temperature"
Economic Daily · China Economic Net reporter Lin Huocan
In the first half of this year, in the face of the impact of the new crown pneumonia epidemic, China made overall efforts to promote epidemic prevention and control and economic and social development. The situation of epidemic prevention and control continued to improve, and the steady economic recovery was obvious. The employment and price performance closely related to people's livelihood were generally stable, and the Chinese economy handed over a report card of economic operation with temperature.
In the first two months of this year, the surveyed unemployment rate increased.
Especially in February, the production and operation activities of many enterprises were basically in a state of shutdown, the employment demand of enterprises decreased, recruitment was delayed or cancelled, and the unemployment rate surveyed in cities and towns increased.
With the gradual improvement of the epidemic prevention and control situation, the production and living order of the whole society has been continuously restored.
The CPC Central Committee adheres to the general tone of seeking progress while maintaining stability, further strengthens the hedging of macro policies, comprehensively strengthens the employment priority policy, and actively promotes the work of assisting enterprises to stabilize posts and expand employment.
China has increased policies to hedge and stabilize jobs, played a combination of "relief, relief, and compensation" policies, reduced and exempted the contributions of three social insurance units in stages, allowed to postpone the payment of social insurance premiums, expanded the benefits of the policy of stable post return of unemployment insurance for small and medium-sized enterprises and replacing training with workers, and provided absorption subsidies and internship subsidies for enterprises to absorb the employment of key groups.
With the implementation of various policies to stabilize employment, the employment demand of enterprises has steadily rebounded, the employment situation has gradually improved, and the surveyed unemployment rate in cities and towns has gradually decreased. In June, the surveyed unemployment rate was 5.7%.
Zhang Yi, director of the Department of Population and Employment Statistics of the National Bureau of Statistics, said that in the second quarter, various employment policies continued to take effect, and the labor force that withdrew due to the impact of the epidemic returned one after another. The urban labor participation rate in June increased by about 10 percentage points compared with February, which was close to the level of the same period last year.
Data show that the total urban employment in June increased by more than 19% compared with February, and most industries reached the pre-epidemic level; The average weekly working hours of employees in enterprises reached 46.8 hours, 6.6 hours higher than in February and 0.1 hours higher than in January.
Prices are also related to thousands of households.
In January this year, CPI rose by 5.4% year-on-year, setting a new high for many years.
In February, although the year-on-year increase of CPI fell slightly, it was still in the "5 range."
The year-on-year increase of CPI is at a high level, which is not only driven by consumer demand before the Spring Festival, but also by the wrong month of the Spring Festival and a low year-on-year base.
However, the impact of the new crown pneumonia epidemic on prices is particularly obvious.
Affected by the prevention and control of the epidemic, logistics delays, untimely material supply and increased material transportation costs occurred all over the country in January and February. In addition, some citizens hoarded and snapped up, and the prices of some daily necessities increased significantly.
In order to cope with the disturbance brought by epidemic prevention and control to the price situation, relevant departments have brought important living materials into the scope of emergency transportation guarantee to ensure smooth transportation of materials.
Under the action of a series of policy measures, the market supply of vegetables and fruits has been strongly guaranteed.
In response to the rapid rise in pork prices at the beginning of this year, after the central government issued the policy of ensuring supply and stabilizing prices, all regions and departments quickly implemented it, and the supply of pork reserves was significantly improved, pig production capacity was restored in an orderly manner, and the production and marketing order was gradually normal.
Since March, pork prices have continued to decline, and the year-on-year increase in food prices fell back to 10.6% in May; In June, pork prices rose slightly month-on-month due to factors such as the slowdown in pig production, the decrease in import volume and the rebound in group consumption demand.
The seasonal changes of fresh vegetable prices are obvious, with an average increase of 3.4% in the first half of the year.
Affected by the high base of comparison in the same period last year, the price of fresh fruit continued to decline year on year, with an average decline of 13.3% in the first half of the year.
The basic livelihood of the people has been effectively guaranteed, and the overall economic and social situation has remained stable and orderly.
With the gradual recovery of transportation and logistics, all localities have increased their efforts to ensure supply, and the market supply and demand situation has improved.
Since March, CPI has declined for four consecutive months, and the year-on-year increase has also dropped from 4.3% in March to 2.5% in June, and the overall price level has returned to stability.
In the second half of the year, China's prices will continue to maintain a moderate level, and the overall inflationary pressure is not great. However, it is still necessary to promote the restoration of production and living order on the premise of normalizing epidemic prevention and control.
Effectively respond to natural disasters such as floods and droughts in major agricultural production areas such as grain, fruits and vegetables, strengthen market supervision, and resolutely crack down on hoarding, price gouging and other behaviors that disrupt market order.
