BEIJING, Hainan, Qinghai, July 26 (Xinhua) Title: "Flower Sea Live Room" by Qinghai Lake: "Sweet" Brings Goods to Help Farmers Increase Income
Author Hu Guilong Pan Yujie
"In midsummer, Qinghai Lake is full of golden flowers and thousands of bees flying. Here, the altitude is higher, the temperature difference between day and night is large, and the air pollution is less. The strong light breeds the most tenacious and generous bee colony, creating Qinghai royal jelly with high activity, high protein, rich nutritional value, low sugar and low fat characteristics."
On the 26th, Zhang Jianxun, deputy director of the Industry and Information Administration of Hainan Tibetan Autonomous Prefecture, Qinghai Province, said.
On the same day, the live broadcast of bee products was held on the banks of Qinghai Lake. The China Bee Products Association, representatives of entrepreneurs, bee farmers and other parties gathered to jointly promote Qinghai characteristic bee products. A total of nearly 10,000 bottles of Qinghai Plateau royal jelly were sold online and offline, with a total amount of nearly 3.8 million yuan.
The picture shows bee farmers showing bee products on the spot.
It is reported that this live delivery activity uses Beijing Houdeli Bee Industry Chain Store Network, Express Hand, Taobao and other well-known domestic bee product retail enterprises, live broadcast, and e-commerce platforms to promote the exchange and cooperation of "enterprises + beekeepers + growers," and continues to issue "Qinghai Plateau Spring Pulp Consumption Vouchers" to consumers through online and offline channels. It is estimated that the total profit of enterprises for the whole year will be nearly 5.28 million yuan.
In this regard, Wu Na, president of Beijing Houdeli Bee Industry Co., Ltd. thinks it is "very worthwhile": "This move can expand the popularity of Qinghai bee products, attract more consumers to understand and like bee products without adding pure nature, and drive bee farmers to increase their income."
At present, the company has signed production cooperation strategic agreements with Qinghai Cloud Bee Industry Co., Ltd. and Qinghai Huabao Bee Industry Co., Ltd., hoping to jointly promote the rapid development of Qinghai's local bee industry.
The picture shows the sea of rape flowers by Qinghai Lake.
This spring, due to the need to set up road checkpoints for epidemic prevention and control, beekeepers' journey of "chasing flowers and honey" was blocked. Many bees died due to missing the flowering period and lack of food, and beekeepers' income was seriously affected.
"All the year round, beekeepers travel long distances with the flowering period, moving all the way north from Yunnan and Sichuan to the northwest. They live in the open air and have no fixed place to live. It is very hard.
As enterprises, we have a responsibility to help them. "
Wu Na said.
"Little bees are 'environmental scouts' and bees can't survive in heavily polluted areas." Zhao Xiaochuan, executive vice president of China Bee Products Association, said that bee pollination is an important link in the ecological chain and plays an irreplaceable role in protecting plant diversity and improving the ecological environment.
At the same time, bee pollination can increase the yield and quality of crops, especially in areas with wide planting and poor management conditions, pollination is of greater significance.
Research data show that pollination can increase rape yield by about 15% -30%.
The picture shows Zhao Xiaochuan (right), executive vice president of China Bee Products Association, promoting Qinghai bee products.
"The economic, ecological and social benefits created by bee pollination are far greater than the value of bee products themselves. The bee industry has great potential in human health, crop production, vegetation reproduction and ecological protection, but people have always known little about it."
Zhao Xiaochuan said.
Nowadays, the number of beekeepers is getting smaller and smaller. In addition to beekeepers who travel all the year round, there are still many poor households with mobility difficulties who choose to invest in cooperatives with beehives.
"The state has financial support. We contact technical personnel to help guide. Bee farmers lack understanding and judgment of the market environment. To open up sales, they also need the help and coordination of the government, enterprises and industry associations."
Zhao Xiaochuan said.
"I hope everyone will pay more attention to and help beekeeping groups in the future," Wu Na said. "Our bee products are also screened and controlled in strict accordance with national standards to ensure quality and protect consumer rights while helping beekeepers."
