Yang Hongnian, founder of Beijing Philharmonic Choir, died at the age of 86
Beijing News (Reporter Liu Zhen) On July 26, the Beijing Philharmonic Chorus published an obituary. Yang Hongnian, founder of the Beijing Philharmonic Chorus, a famous Chinese conductor, music educator, lifelong academic member of the Central Conservatory of Music and professor of the command department, died in Beijing at 13: 55 on July 26, 2020 at the age of 86.
The picture is from the official website of Beijing Philharmonic Choir.
Yang Hongnian was born in 1934 in Nanjing, Jiangsu Province. He loved music since childhood.
In 1951, he was the conductor of the chorus of Nanjing People's Radio. In the autumn of 1951, he was admitted to the Music Department of East China Normal University in Shanghai. He studied conducting from Professor Yang Jiaren and German conductor Hitzmann, and studied musical style and polyphony from former Soviet expert Arzamanov.
In 1958, he taught in the Music Department of Beijing Art Normal College, and in 1973, he was transferred to the Composition Department and Command Department of the Central Conservatory of Music.
Yang Hongnian founded the Beijing Philharmonic Choir in 1983.
For more than 30 years, adhering to the tenet of "love and dedication," he led the choir to sing all over the world and won dozens of awards in important competitions at home and abroad.
He has conducted the performances of more than 30 groups, including the Central Orchestra Chorus, the Central National Song and Dance Troupe, the Oriental Song and Dance Troupe and the Shanghai Chorus, and held many symphonic concerts and chorus concerts.
His works include "Band Training," "Chorus Training," "Two Song Writing," "Children's Song Collection" (Volume I and Volume II), and his papers "On Chorus Intonation," "On the Sound Layout of Orchestra," as well as his translations "Chorus Orchestration" and "Debussy's Harmony Language."

































































































































